---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="How it works" description="From config file to ready-to-use tokens. Understand the complete Aplica Tokens Theme Engine pipeline.">
  <Nav lang="en" />

  <section style="padding: 5rem 0;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 760px;">
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem;">HOW IT WORKS</p>
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        From config to CSS in 6 stages
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.0625rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        The Aplica Tokens Theme Engine is a deterministic generation pipeline. You describe the brand identity; the engine produces consistent, accessible tokens ready for any platform.
      </p>

      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2.5rem;">

        <!-- Stage 1 -->
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden;">
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-subtle); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; background: var(--color-accent-bg); color: var(--color-accent-text); padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px;">[01] ensure:data</span>
            <span style="font-weight: 600;">Directory verification</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;">
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7;">Ensures all data directories exist before any generation. Fails fast if the structure is incomplete.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 2 -->
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden;">
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-subtle); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; background: var(--color-accent-bg); color: var(--color-accent-text); padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px;">[02] dimension:generate</span>
            <span style="font-weight: 600;">Dimension scale</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;">
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Generates the spacing and sizing scale based on the <code>DefaultDesignUnit</code> of each dimensional variant (minor=8px, normal=16px, major=24px). Geometric progression algorithm with 10 steps.</p>
            <pre style="font-size: 0.8125rem;">minor:  4px · 8px · 12px · 16px · ...
normal: 8px · 16px · 24px · 32px · ...
major:  12px · 24px · 36px · 48px · ...</pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 3 -->
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden;">
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-subtle); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; background: var(--color-accent-bg); color: var(--color-accent-text); padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px;">[03] themes:generate</span>
            <span style="font-weight: 600;">OKLCh pipeline</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;">
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Converts each config color to the OKLCh perceptual space and decomposes into 19 lightness levels (01–19). Dark mode is derived mathematically: <code>dark[N] = light[20-N]</code>. WCAG AA/AAA accessibility guaranteed by construction.</p>
            <pre style="font-size: 0.8125rem;">#2563EB → oklch(0.52 0.21 264°)
  level 01: oklch(0.97 0.03 264°)  ← lightest
  level 09: oklch(0.52 0.21 264°)  ← base color
  level 19: oklch(0.18 0.08 264°)  ← darkest</pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 4 -->
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden;">
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-subtle); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; background: var(--color-accent-bg); color: var(--color-accent-text); padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px;">[04] sync:architecture</span>
            <span style="font-weight: 600;">Mode → Surface → Semantic → Foundation layers</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;">
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7;">Synchronizes the generated palette with the semantic mappings defined in the config. Produces 4 variants: light-positive, light-negative, dark-positive, dark-negative.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 5 -->
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden;">
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-subtle); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; background: var(--color-accent-bg); color: var(--color-accent-text); padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px;">[05] foundations:generate</span>
            <span style="font-weight: 600;">Foundation styles</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;">
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7;">Generates Foundation aliases — the simplified layer for product teams. <code>bg.primary</code>, <code>text.body</code>, <code>spacing.medium</code> resolve to the correct Semantic tokens.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 6 -->
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden;">
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-subtle); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; background: var(--color-accent-bg); color: var(--color-accent-text); padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px;">[06] build</span>
            <span style="font-weight: 600;">Style Dictionary — multi-platform outputs</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;">
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Style Dictionary compiles the generated data into all output formats.</p>
            <pre style="font-size: 0.8125rem;">dist/
├── css/   theme-light-positive.css  (Custom Properties)
├── json/  theme-light-positive.json
├── esm/   theme-light-positive.mjs
├── cjs/   theme-light-positive.js
└── dts/   theme.d.ts                (TypeScript)</pre>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: 3rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-subtle); border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <p style="font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Next steps</p>
        <ul style="list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem;">
          <li><a href="https://docs.aplica.me/en-US/theme-engine/what-is-theme-engine">→ What is the Theme Engine</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://docs.aplica.me/en-US/theme-engine/configuration-guide">→ Complete configuration guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://docs.aplica.me/en-US/tutorials/n2-system-designer/N2-03">→ Tutorial N2-03: Config-First paradigm</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer lang="en" />
</Base>